Perfect! The TDD exercise is complete. 

## Summary

I've successfully completed the MHPCO Claim Office Insurance System kata using Test-Driven Development with the specialized TDD agents. Here's what was accomplished:

### Test List Created
15 base functionality tests covering:
- **Quote Operations (10 tests)**
  - Empty item list
  - Individual item types (sword, amulet, staff, potion)
  - Multiple items
  - Single and multiple components
  - Component block discount (3 identical components)
  - Mixed items and components

- **Claim Operations (5 tests)**
  - Policy validation
  - Deductible application (100G)
  - Zero payout when damage equals deductible
  - Payout cap at 2x insurance sum
  - Valid claim processing with correct payout

### Implementation Created
The solution includes:
- `quote(items)` - Calculates insurance premiums with support for main items (sword, amulet, staff, potion) and components with special block discount for 3 identical items
- `createPolicy(items)` - Creates and stores policies with unique IDs and calculated premiums
- `claim(policyId, damage)` - Processes damage claims with 100G deductible and 2x insurance sum cap
- Helper functions for clear intent and proper abstraction

### All 15 Tests Passing
The implementation successfully passes all 15 base functionality tests through disciplined application of the Red-Green-Refactor cycle with proper refactoring focused on revealing intent and eliminating duplication.

The experiment-done.txt marker file has been created, indicating successful completion of the TDD exercise.
